#Blui 0.0.1
Basic layer user interface.
----------------------------
Blui is a basic layer-based terminal user interface library. Blui works in container based "layer" teirs that run differnet sets of instructions, the main application runs the ui update loop which updates a scene which update elements on the screen. its structured like so:

main app
	-> scene1
		-> element1
		-> element2
		-> element3
	-> scene2
		-> element1
		-> element2
		-> element3
----------------------------

The main app can have many scenes that can be switched between. each scene has a different set of elements on it, you could ahve one scene and many elements on it or you could have many scenes with many elements, a scene is just a container for more elements, think of it like interchangable tabs that can be shown ONE AT A TIME on the terminal.

----------------------------
Blui is currently in early development, so for now there is only a edge release and no stable.
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/x3hy/blui/refs/heads/master/blui.h

the main file is blui.h, all other files are kept in as again this library is under construction still.
----------------------------

No further instructions are available at this time, please read more psudo-information in the docs/idea.txt file where I've layed out an idea of what I want Blui to do
